Source: handbrake
Section: graphics
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Christian Marillat <marillat@debian.org>
Bugs: mailto:marillat@debian.org
Homepage: http://www.handbrake.fr/
Standards-Version: 3.8.0
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 7), jam, libhal-storage-dev, wget, libgtkhtml3.14-dev,
 quilt, libfaac-dev, libfaad-dev, libxvidcore4-dev, libtheora-dev, libmp3lame-dev,
 libmkv-dev, subversion, automake, intltool, libtool, yasm [amd64 i386], libbz2-dev,
 libsamplerate0-dev, libdvdread-dev, libvorbis-dev

Package: handbrake-cli
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: versatile DVD ripper and video transcoder - command line
 HandBrake is a versatile, easy-to-use tool for converting DVDs and other
 videos into H.264, XViD, or OGG formatted media.  It's particularly useful
 for making videos that are compatible with portable video devices such as
 the Apple iPod/iPhone or Sony PSP.  This package contains the command-line
 variant, HandBrakeCLI

Package: handbrake-gtk
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: versatile DVD ripper and video transcoder - GTK GUI
 HandBrake is a versatile, easy-to-use tool for converting DVDs and other
 videos into H.264, XViD, or OGG formatted media. It's particularly useful
 for making videos that are compatible with portable video devices such as
 the Apple iPod/iPhone or Sony PSP. This package contains the graphical
 variant, ghb.
